<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9174> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9174" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 726, footnote 18" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7658> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7658" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent as legatus to Hannibal in 219 and to Carthage in 218; see MRR 1.237 and 239. The spelling Tampilus in Cic. Phil. 5.27, as late as 43 B.C., may be a deliberate archaism (Shackleton Bailey, Onom.)\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1312> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1312" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These men, defined by Livy as maiores natu, were sent to Carthage with Rome's ultimatum (Liv. 21.18.1, cf. 21.19.6, and 20.9; Dio fr. 55.10; Zon. 8.22; cf. Polyb. 3.20.6 and 9, and 33.1-4, and 40.2; Frontin. Str. 1.11.4; Sil. Ital. 2.1-390; App. Ib. 13)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1311> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1311" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 219, Legates, Ambassadors." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1292> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1292" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "According to Cicero (Phil. 5.27) and Livy (21.6.8), these were sent to Saguntum to order Hannibal to desist from the siege. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 38, no. 16." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1291> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1291" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "From Livy it would appear that these Envoys were dispatched under the Consuls of 218 (Liv. 21.6.3), but as Saguntum fell before the winter of 219-218, and the arrival of the Envoys may well have preceded Hannibal's attack (Polyb. 3.15.4), the date is at the latest early in 219." .
